                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc ana="#slab">
                            <supportDesc ana="#stone.marble">
                                <support>
                                    <p>
                                        <seg type="material">marble</seg>
                                        <seg type="form">broken slab</seg>
                                    </p>
                                        <dimensions type="surface" unit="cm">
                                            <width>36.4</width>
                                            <height>32.2</height>
                                            <depth>2.0</depth>
                                        </dimensions>            
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#fragments.contig">
                                    <p>The slab, broken vertically down the middle, has been reassembled and plastered within a wooden frame. Smaller cracks may be found at the edges. The top, right, and bottom edges show signs of wear and are chipped away in places, but roughly straight. The bottom edge may perhaps have been broken but no text appears to be missing. The left edge lips up forming a raised stripe, ca. 0.1 cm. high and ca. 1.5 cm wide. This was not polished smooth, however, and it is unclear whether it was raised higher before being broken off, it is simply all that remains of a border missing on the other sides, or the slab was possibly reused and the text added later.</p>
                                </condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout columns="1" writtenLines="6">
                                    <p>The first line is centered. The second line begins flush left, 0.5 cm from the raised edge, with each line thereafter increasingly indented. Line 4 and 5 also appear to be roughly centred.</p>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc ana="#impressed.inscribed.chiseled">
                            <p>  The horizontal strokes of the letters T, L, and F appear rustic, especially the crossbar of the T, which extends further to the right and rises upwards.</p>
                        </handDesc>
